Upvoted for possibly stupid reasons, listed below:

My username was derived from ancestors I no longer share a name with. This was, for all points and purposes, a shoutout to my own family and that makes me disproportionately happy.
I did research on aforementioned ancestors a while back and have read a little (meaning the Wikipedia article) about Clan MacLeod's Fairy Flag and was super psyched to see such an obscure piece of real-world lore included on the site.
The implications provided here are, well, pretty great, even if my excitement has been inflated by my personal investment in the piece. My conclusions were pretty similar to Bill's, above, and that sort of narrative also appeals to me.


So maybe I'm openly letting pre-existing biases get in the way here, but I found the piece to be really fun.







